'''Softpedia''' is a site that indexes information and provides downloads for many games, drivers, mobile phones, and software for the Windows, Macintosh, and Linux platforms, as well as [[Personal digital assistant|PDAs]] and other devices. The site also indexes major technology, science, health, and entertainment news both from ticker servers and from in-house sources. As of April 2007, it is one of the top 500 websites according to [[Alexa Internet|Alexa]] [[web traffic|traffic]] rankings.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.alexa.com/data/details/?url=www.softpedia.com |title=SoftPedia.com |accessdate=2007-04-24 |year=2007 |work=[[Alexa Internet|Alexa]]}}</ref> The site was originally known as Softnews.ro, but was changed to Softpedia near the end of 2003.{{Fact|date=April 2007}}
